<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>A Queensland woman has been dragged into bushland and sexually assaulted while out for a morning walk.</p>

<p>The 66-year-old woman was walking on a pathway next to the Ross River in Townsville about 6am on Wednesday when she was grabbed by an unknown man.</p>

<p>'She was dragged into the bushland just off the walkway and sexually assaulted,' Senior Sergeant Scot Warrick told reporters.</p>

<p>'While not elderly, she is a vulnerable person of some age.'</p>

<p>The woman called triple-zero after the assault.</p>

<p>She suffered serious facial injuries and was taken to the Townsville University Hospital for treatment.</p>

<p>The man is described as having a large build.</p>

<p>'This is possibly an opportunistic (attack),' Snr Sgt Warrick said.</p>

<p>'We are taking this extremely seriously.'</p>

<p>A crime scene has been set up at scene.</p>
